    "recap_url": "https://www.bgsufalcons.com/news/2026/3/14/baseball-falcons-tally-10-0-win-over-miami-oh-for-first-shutout-in-oxford-since-2014",
    "recap_headline": "Bowling Green State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "OXFORD, Ohio\n\u2013\nThe Bowling Green State University baseball team bounced back with a 10-0 run-rule victory over the Miami (OH) RedHawks on Saturday (March 14) to even the series and set up a rubber match on Sunday (March 15). The Falcons started off hot with four runs in the first inning, sparking the offense.\nGriffin Scheiderer\nscored four times and tallied two doubles while\nSam Seidel\nhad three hits and\nVinny Salvione\nhad three RBI. As for the mound,\nNate Kress\npicked up his third win of the season behind five shutout innings and a career-high eight strikeouts.\nCJ Boudreaux\nand\nTitus Lotz\nfinished off the shutout on the mound with the trio combining for 12 strikeouts in the win. The shutout marks the first for Bowling Green since April 27, 2024.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nGriffin Scheiderer\ndrew a lead off walk for the Falcons followed by a\nSam Seidel\nsingle to quickly put runners at the corners for BGSU.\nAnthony Mitta\nfollowed with a single through the right side, bringing home Scheiderer for a 1-0 lead before the first out was recorded.\nVinny Salvione\nkept the rally going with a double into left field, bringing home Seidel from second. A grounder by\nTJ Takats\nfollowed in the next at-bat and was enough to score Mitta. Later in the inning,\nCarter Mottice\nlegged out an infield single that was enough to score Salvione, pushing the Bowling Green advantage to 4-0 after the top of the first.\nIn the second inning,\nZack Horky\nreached on an error and stole second. He was joined on the base paths by Scheiderer, drawing a walk, before a bunt single from Seidel loaded the bases with no outs. Mitta ripped a liner up the middle off the leg of the pitcher. Miami fielded the ball for an out, but Horky scored in the process for a 5-0 tally.\nA walk to Salvione loaded the bases again with a passed ball moving each runner up, including Scheiderer home for a 6-0 score.\nAfter a scoreless third, the Falcons went back to work in the fourth. Scheiderer led off with a double to deep left center followed by a Seidel walk. A Mitta grounder moved the runners up and brought the infield in. Salvione knocked a single past the infielders, bringing in both Scheiderer and Seidel for an 8-0 advantage.\nThe Falcons put together a two-out rally in the seventh.\nAndrew DiLodovico\nsingled up the middle followed by a walk to Mottice. A single to left by\nBrayden Curlis\nscored DiLodovico for a 9-0 lead.\nScheiderer led off the eighth inning with his second double of the day, Seidel doubled through the right side, switching places with Scheiderer for a 10-0 score.\nSTAT LEADERS\nNate Kress\n: W (3-0), 5.0 IP, 5 H, 0 R/ER, 8 K\nCJ Boudreaux\n: 2.0 IP, 1 H, 0 R/ER, 2 K\nTitus Lotz\n: 1.0 IP, 1 H, 0 R/ER, 2 K\nGriffin Scheiderer\n: 2-for-3, 2 2B, 4 R, 2 BB\nSam Seidel\n: 3-for-4, 1 2B, 2 R, 1 RBI, 1 BB\nVinny Salvione\n: 2-for-4, 3 RBI, 1 R, 1 BB\nAnthony Mitta\n: 1-for-5, 2 RBI, 1 R\nCarter Mottice\n: 1-for-3, 1 RBI, 1 BB\nFALCON STAT FACTS\nThe shutout for the Falcons is the first since April 27, 2024 at Kent State, also a 10-0 final. The shutout is the first against Miami (OH) since May 18, 2021 with a 2-0 final. It is also the first shutout in Oxford for BGSU since May 4, 2014 with a 5-0 win.\nNate Kress\nput together a strong start for the Falcons, hurling five scoreless frames. Kress struck out eight in the outing, a new career-high after striking out a previous career-high of five last weekend. Kress picked up his third win of the season, giving him the win in three of BGSU's five victories this year.\nAt the plate,\nGriffin Scheiderer\nstepped into the leadoff role for the first time and delivered the best game of his BGSU career so far. Scheiderer tallied his first two career doubles and drew two walks, scoring each time he reached for four runs scored in the game.\nSam Seidel\nadded his second three-hit game of the season, adding a double, two RBI and a run scored.\nVinny Salvione\nregistered a two-hit day for the Falcons, including a team-high three RBI. Salvione now has an eight-game hitting streak, the longest active on the team. Salvione also has back-to-back games with three RBI.\nAnthony Mitta\nregistered a hit and two RBI for the Falcons. He's now logged a hit in 12 of BGSU's last 13 games.\nCJ Boudreaux\nthrew two shutout innings of relief for the Falcons, giving him three consecutive appearances without allowing a run that spans 3.2 innings of work.\nEntering the game, Bowling Green had scored four runs in the first inning this season. The Falcons doubled that total with four runs in the first frame.\nUP NEXT\nBowling Green and Miami (OH) will conclude the series with a 1 p.m. first pitch on Sunday (March 15) in Oxford.\nAny schedule changes will be announced on BGSUFalcons.com as well as Twitter/X (@BGSU_Baseball).\nFollow the Falcons\nBe sure to follow the Falcons' baseball team on social media\nTwitter - @BGSU_Athletics and @BGSU_Baseball\nInstagram - 'bgfalcons' and 'bgsu_baseball'\nFacebook - 'BGSU Athletics'\nYouTube - 'Falcons Athletics'"
